Prerequisites
=============

LibLunar-gtk requires Gtk+-2.16.x libraries.
PyGtk 2.16.x are required to enable python binding support.

Simple install procedure
========================

  $ tar -zxf liblunar-gtk-@LIBLUNAR_GTK_VERSION@.tar.gz              # unpack the sources
  $ cd liblunar-gtk-@LIBLUNAR_GTK_VERSION@                           # change to the toplevel directory
  $ ./configure                                 # run the `configure' script
  $ make                                        # build liblunar-gtk
  [ Become root if necessary ]
  $ sudo make install                           # install liblunar-gtk

if you want to use LunarCalendar to replace the GtkCalendar, please edit this file like that:

$ cat /etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc.d/99-liblunar-preload 
#!/bin/sh
LD_PRELOAD="/usr/lib/liblunar-gtk-preload.so"
export LD_PRELOAD

and change the mode like that, then restart X.
$ chmod +x /etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc.d/99-liblunar-preload
